public interface XTerm<T extends XType>

XTerms are used to represent the terms occurring in constraints. They are the building blocks of Constraints. This interface is the root of other XTerm interfaces. All XTerms contain type information represented by the type parameter T. Note that the type associated with the XTerm cannot itself have constraints, and must be a base type.

Author:
lshadare
